collections.description:
The first existence, Nythos, formed his consciousness from a single pulse of information. His awareness expanded in a world without the concept of space, generating new waves in its wake. Nythos could alter his own form through thought and create beings similar to himself.

Creation in this realm did not follow the laws of physics as we know them. There was no force, mass, gravity, or electromagnetism. Only the exchange and transformation of information maintained the order of this world. Beings were composed of information waves vibrating at different frequencies, and those that resonated at the same frequency could merge or separate at will.

collections.name: Prophecies
collections.description:
"Art does not predict the future, it reveals it."

Prophecies is a collection of original art on canvas, captured digitally, that revives the intensity of Neo-Expressionism in a new context. Each work is a raw and emotional manifestation, capturing prophetic visions through vibrant colors.

Each piece is born on the physical canvas, through mixed techniques, dynamic textures and layers of color, the work comes to life in its purest form. Then, each creation is digitized in high resolution, preserving every detail and original stroke, to finally be transformed into a unique NFT within the Web3 ecosystem.

This series fuses analog and digital, bringing physical art to the decentralized universe. Each NFT is more than just a visual piece: it is a portal to a unique narrative, where passion and intuition meet in a space without rules or restrictions.

collections.name: The 10th E State - Drawings
collections.description: The 10th E State drawings exist in a space between revelation and erasure, where gestural abstraction becomes a means of capturing the unseen forces shaping contemporary existence. These works are not just studies of figures or environments but investigations into distortion itself—where the act of drawing mirrors the fragmentation of reality under systems of control. Forms flicker between presence and absence, lines collapse into smears, and textures evoke both forensic evidence and administrative redactions. The urgency in mark-making suggests something both archival and unstable, as if these images were extracted from a document in the process of being erased. There is a refusal to resolve into clarity, an insistence on ambiguity that makes the 10th E State an ongoing record of power, surveillance, and the spaces in between.

collections.name: Pictures of cornary spasmatic angina pectoris
collections.description:
「悪質冠攣縮性狭心症と映えない日常」

この症状はかなり悪質だ（中略）。主治医は言った。私の中にもうひとり別人格がいると思えと。それを主治医は狭心症と呼んだり自律神経と呼んだりするのだが。別人格なら私ではないのだから、私と切り離して見てやろう。「こいつ」「そいつ」などと呼び、私は敵対することにした。なだめたりなんかしない。
　更に主治医からは、私の「治したい」と思う気迫は10代のそれだと言われた。ならば別人格に売られた喧嘩に対して黙っているわけにはいかない。ティーンエイジャーなだけでなく、この歳でヤンキーになった。喧嘩上等といきがってはいるものの何度も何度も「そいつ」にボコボコにされている。

　そこで、私はこの病によって堕とされた自分の姿と生活を撮り、「こいつ」が私にした悪事を白日の下に晒してやることにした。ゲラゲラ笑い、パジャマのまま着替えられず、カメラを持ってふざけながら。時にリアルに発作を起こしながら。

「冠攣縮性狭心症の野郎ども！こっちが50代だからってなぁ、いつまでもなめたマネしてんじゃねえぞ。5年もボコボコにしやがってもう充分だろうが！。これ以上はもう勘弁できねぇ。今度襲って来やがったらただじゃおかねぇがらな！！！！」

collections.name: FLORAL METAMORPHOSIS
collections.description:
At the boundary between reality and imagination, flowers undergo a digital metamorphosis, taking on new and unexpected forms. Floral Metamorphosis is a limited-edition NFT collection where photography and digital manipulation merge to create a visionary universe.

Starting from real flower photographs, Elena Rivautella transforms nature through digital techniques, revealing surreal figures: a whirling dervish, an ethereal fish, and abstract shapes that challenge perception. Each piece invites the viewer to look beyond the ordinary and embrace artistic reinvention.

This collection is for those who love art that surprises, transforming the familiar into the extraordinary. It’s also ideal for collectors seeking unique, thought-provoking works that reveal different narratives depending on the observer’s perspective.
